An Embu man has been charged with breaking into houses and stealing panties. The man, who has a pending case of stealing panties was today charged with breaking into another house and taking away six panties. He did not steal any other thing. Dickson Githinji was charged before Embu Senior Resident Magistrate Tony Kwambai. In the charge sheet, it is  said that on May 28,2020 at around 5.30pm at Mikimbi Village, Githinji broke into Juliet Nyaga’s house and stole her panties worth Sh1,500. He pleaded not guilty before seeking to be released on bond. The Magistrate freed the accused on Sh15,000 bond and surety of similar amount. The case will be mentioned on June 29, 2020.